name: HTMLMeterElement
description: The HTML <meter> elements expose the HTMLMeterElement interface, which provides special properties and methods (beyond the HTMLElement object interface they also have available to them by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of <meter> elements.

members.name: HTMLMeterElement.high
members.description: A double representing the value of the high boundary, reflecting the high attribute.

members.name: HTMLMeterElement.low
members.description: A double representing the value of the low boundary, reflecting the lowattribute.

members.name: HTMLMeterElement.max
members.description: A double representing the maximum value, reflecting the max attribute.

members.name: HTMLMeterElement.min
members.description: A double representing the minimum value, reflecting the min attribute.

members.name: HTMLMeterElement.optimum
members.description: A double representing the optimum, reflecting the optimum attribute.

members.name: HTMLMeterElement.labels
members.description: A NodeList of <label> elements that are associated with the element.
